  "body":"*If you aren't sure about your bug, you can always join our [Discord](https://discord.gg/HNmxvpm) and ask in #agora or #engineering!*\r\n\r\n**Problem**\r\n\r\nWhen using arrow keys to navigate up and down through the list of search results, the list does not automatically scroll as you move past the first few items. The user is unable to see which search result is currently selected.\r\n\r\n**Expected Behavior**\r\n\r\nLike Roam, when you select a search result is that is initially beyond the visible items, the search result list should scroll to bring the selection into view.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\n\r\nhttps://athensresearch.github.io/athens/ then load test data, search for a term in Athena and use the arrow keys to go down the result list.\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\n\r\nhttps://www.loom.com/share/90714b294cdb4c77a0d2f69d1fe56396\r\n",
