      "created_at":"2020-07-19 00:23:59 UTC",
      "updated_at":"2020-07-19 01:27:14 UTC",
      "author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body":"> Should list wrap around? i.e. if you press up at index 0 or press down at index N.\r\n\r\nThat's the current implementation in roam. Wrote up some quick code so that key up/down wrap around\r\n\r\n```clojure\r\n(= key KeyCodes.UP)\r\n      (swap! state update :index #(dec (if (= 0 %) (count results) %)))\r\n\r\n(= key KeyCodes.DOWN)\r\n      (swap! state update :index #(if (= (- (count results) 1) %) 0 (inc %)))\r\n```",
      "performed_via_github_app":null
    },
